President Biden and Prime Minister Bennett of Israel had a phone call to discuss shared security challenges, particularly regarding Iran and its proxies. They highlighted their strong personal bond and how it has helped both countries reach common positions on difficult issues. President Biden welcomed the visit of the Prime Minister's National Security Advisor to Washington and accepted an invitation to visit Israel in the future. He also acknowledged the ongoing efforts between Israeli and Palestinian officials to lower tensions during Ramadan. President Biden reaffirmed his support for Israel's defense needs and welcomed the allocation of $1 billion to replenish Israel's Iron Dome system. Both leaders committed to staying in regular contact through the U.S-Israel Strategic Consultative Group.